jobs.description:
We are looking for a Test Engineer to join our Lithuanian team! 
· Do you have a strong engineering affinity with a passion for manual and automation testing whilst collaborating with product teams?
· We are looking for someone who is highly collaborative, analytical and results orientated!

Who we are: 
SAI360 is giving companies a new perspective on risk management. By integrating Governance, Risk, Compliance (GRC) software and Ethics & Compliance Learning resources, SAI360 can broaden your risk horizon and increase your ability to identify, manage, and mitigate risk. See risk from every angle. Visit www.sai360.com .

Think you’re a fit for SAI360? 
As a Test Engineer, you will be using the Cypress framework to automate repeatable test scenarios to add value across our new and existing innovative solutions in the GRC domain.
You will be a part of a global team that is responsible for the continuous development of our solutions. The team is composed of product managers, user experience designers, and developers.
You enjoy working in an agile team and you want to contribute to the continuous improvement of the performance of your scrum team and the quality of our product. You will also be part of a lively development community who bring loads of experience to the table, giving you the opportunity to learn and grow.

The primary objectives and responsibilities of a Test Engineer includes:
· Ensure the quality and reliability of software products through both manual and automated testing;
· Collaborate with development and product teams to understand requirements and support high-quality software releases;
· Design, implement, and maintain effective test plans, test cases, and automation scripts;
· Identify, document, and track defects through to resolution in close cooperation with development teams;
· Conduct functional, regression, and integration testing;
· Maintain clear and up-to-date test documentation and report test outcomes effectively;
· Collaborate with developers and product managers in agile teams to ensure quality is embedded throughout the development lifecycle;
· Participate in code reviews and contribute to the evolution of QA best practices.

What you’ll bring to the table: 
· Previous experience in software testing or quality assurance with a focus on SaaS or GRC solutions would be highly advantageous;
· Experience with both manual testing and test automation tools is critical to success;
· Proficiency in scripting or programming languages such as Java, Python, or JavaScript;
· Hands-on experience with tools like JIRA, Git, Jenkins, or similar;
· Solid understanding of Agile/Scrum development methodologies;
· ISTQB certification is highly advantageous;
· An analytical mindset, with the ability to think outside the box;
· Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English;
· Highly detail-oriented and organised, capable of managing multiple tasks effectively;
· A collaborative team player with a proactive approach and strong sense of ownership;
· Eagerness to learn and adapt quickly in a dynamic environment;
· Positive can do attitude;
· Flexibility – we are a global company with team mates all over the world!

Why you should apply to SAI360: 
Alongside a remote-first hiring strategy and competitive salary package, we offer a wide variety of employee perks including –
· Health Insurance;
· Flexible working hours;
· Accident Insurance;
· Monthly sports allowance;
· Quarterly wellness days;
· Bonus incentive Plan;
· Annual leave as per local law;

As required by applicable Pay Transparency laws, the base salary range for this position is €2083-€2391 gross per month plus opportunities for bonuses or commission. Exact compensation may vary based on skills, experience, and location.
